iversity Press. pp.&#160;177\xe2\x80\x9398.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACode-switching&amp;rft.atitle=Code-switching+and+grammatical+theory&amp;rft.aufirst=Pieter&amp;rft.aulast=Muysken&amp;rft.btitle=One+Speaker%2C+Two+Languages%3A+Cross-disciplinary+Perspectives+on+Code-switching&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.pages=177-98&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Bokamba-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Bokamba_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Bokamba_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Bokamba_4-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Bokamba, Eyamba G. (1989). "Are there syntactic constraints on code-mixing?". <i>World Englishes</i>. <b>8</b> (3): 277\xe2\x80\x9392. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1111%2Fj.1467-971X.1989.tb00669.x">10.1111/j.1467-971X.1989.tb00669.x</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACode-switching&amp;rft.atitle=Are+there+syntactic+constraints+on+code-mixing%3F&amp;rft.aufirst=Eyamba+G.&amp;rft.aulast=Bokamba&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.jtitle=World+Englishes&amp;rft.pages=277-92&amp;rft.volume=8&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-971X.1989.tb00669.x&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Clyne, Michael (2000). "Constraints on code-switching: how universal are they?". In Li Wei. <i>The Bilingualism Reader</i>. Routledge.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACode-switching&amp;rft.atitle=Constraints+on+code-switching%3A+how+universal+are+they%3F&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft.aulast=Clyne&amp;rft.btitle=The+Bilingualism+Reader&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Genessee, Fred (2000). "Early bilingual language development: one language or two?". In Li Wei. <i>The Bilingualism Reader</i>. Routledge.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACode-switching&amp;rft.atitle=Early+bilingual+language+development%3A+one+language+or+two%3F&amp;rft.aufirst=Fred&amp;rft.aulast=Genessee&amp;rft.btitle=The+Bilingualism+Reader&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Weinreich-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Weinreich_7-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Weinreich, Uriel (1953). <i>Languages in Contact</i>. The Hague: Mouton.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACode-switching&amp;rft.aufirst=Uriel&amp;rft.aulast=Weinreich&amp;rft.btitle=Languages+in+Contact&amp;rft.date=1953&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=The+Hague&amp;rft.pub=Mouton&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span 